		  <h1>Overview</h1>
		  <p align="justify">
The evolution of the Large Scale Structures through cosmic time unavoidably leads to nonlinearities and non-Gaussianities in the dark matter and galaxy distribution. Extracting cosmological parameters from the current and next generation of cosmological surveys would therefore require very accurate understading and modeling of the nonlinear Universe. A cosmological analysis limited to the linear scales would never deliver the expected precision measurements of  neutrino masses, dark energy parameters, primordial Non-Gaussianities and other fundamental physics. Most of the information is indeed contained in the clustering on the non-linear scales wich is hard to predict from first principles.  
     </p>
 <p>      
The aim of this workshop is to gather experts in the field of Large Scale structures  to discuss about the prospects of cosmology from nonlinear scales. The format will aim at facilitating as much as possible interaction and informal discussions.
     </p>
 <p>      

Where: <b> Hotel San Martin, Smartno (San Martino), Slovenia </b> <br /> 
When:  <b>July 16-22, 2017</b> 
    <p>
Topics will include perturbation theory, density field reconstruction, numerical simulations, approximate methods, galaxy bias nad others.
     </p>
<p>
<b> Registration is strictly limited to 50 participants </b>.
If you are planning to attend, please register <a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSd54OreBhKKFSmctlFgjMkjpes8iWtJklh8r1MqgIWVC2BNBw/viewform">here</a>.
Registration fees will be included in the hotel reservation.
<br><b>Due to the limited number of participants we can accomodate, registration to the meeting will be confirmed once a hotel reservation will be made through the  main venue</b>. Please see the Accomodation page for more information.
     </p>

<h1>Venue</h1>
		  <p align="justify">
The conference will take place in the beautiful village of <a href="https://goo.gl/maps/WHFhuTapLg72"> Smartno </a> in Slovenia, on the green hills of the region of Brda(Collio), right at the border with Italy. This is one the most important and renowned wine growing regions of the all area. The venue is located in the Hotel San Martin, where a large fraction of the participant will also find accomodation. Additional events, such as wine tasting, an Alpine excursion to Bovec, on the Julian Alps, and a hike along the Rilke path on the coast of Trieste will also be organized. Check the Accomodation page for more info. 
</p>
